The board shall deny a license to any applicant who fails to:
Furnish evidence satisfactory to the board, showing that the individual:
Is at least eighteen (18) years of age;
Has graduated from high school or earned a Kentucky or other state's general educational development (GED) diploma; and
Meets other criteria established by the board through promulgation of administrative regulations;
Verify the information submitted on the application form;
Complete a board-approved training program or course of study involving the performance of home inspections, and pass an examination prescribed or approved by the board;
Submit to the board a certificate of insurance that is acceptable to the board and that:
Is issued by an insurance company or other legal entity authorized to transact insurance business in Kentucky;
Provides for general liability coverage of at least two hundred fifty thousand dollars ($250,000);
Lists the Kentucky Board of Home Inspectors as the certificate holder of any insurance policy satisfying the requirements of this paragraph;
States that cancellation and nonrenewal of the underlying policy is not effective until the board receives at least ten (10) days' prior written notice of the cancellation or nonrenewal; and
Contains any other terms and conditions established by the board; or
Pay a licensing fee established in KRS 198B.706.
